1 2. Whether proposed permanent rules fulfill the legislative
2 intent of the statute that authorized the permanent rulemaking;
3 3. Whether the proposed permanent rules will have a negative
4 impact that is disproportionate to the intended effects of the
5 rulemaking; and
6 4. Whether the agency has the statutory authority to promulgate
7 the proposed permanent rules.
8 C. The Division shall issue a report including the information
9 provided in subsection B of this section, a summary statement of the
10 legislative recommendation being made, and any other information
11 deemed necessary by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
12 Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of the State Senate, and
13 the Administrative Rules Committee Chairs of the Oklahoma House of
14 Representatives and the State Senate.
15 D. The Division may also be responsible for regular evaluations
16 of existing provisions of the administrative code as directed by the
17 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro
18 Tempore of the State Senate, and the Administrative Rules Committee
19 Chairs of the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the State
20 Senate.
